com.netflix.nfgraph

Class NFGraphModelHolder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.netflix.nfgraph.NFGraphModelHolder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>

    public class NFGraphModelHolder
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>
    NFGraphModelHolder maintains an ordering over the models in a given NFGraph.

    An NFGraph may contain one or more "connection models". A "connection model" is a grouping of the set of connections between nodes in the graph.

    If connection models are not specified, a single connection model called "global" will be used to store all connections for a graph. The NFGraph methods which do not specify a connection model use the default "global" connection model.

    Connections added for a connection model will be visible only for that model. Use of multiple connection models will add a minimum of one byte per model-specific connection set per node. As a result, this feature should be used only when the number of connection models is and will remain low.

    It is unlikely that this class will need to be used externally.
